title: Born Of Osiris - Tomorrow We Die Alive (flac) [MentalZero]
description:
Born of Osiris performs deathcore, which is an amalgamation of the metal genres metalcore and death metal, while taking heavy influence from technical and progressive metal, involving frequent use of keyboards, unusual time signatures, synthesizers and programmed electronics. The band cites Cannibal Corpse, Converge, Hatebreed, Slayer, and The Mars Volta as influences. Tomorrow We Die Alive is the fourth full-length album by American deathcore band Born of Osiris. It was released through Sumerian Records on August 20, 2013. The album debuted at 27 on the Billboard 200, selling 13,052 copies in the first week.
